Heat a small pan over a medium heat and add the olive oil. Gently fry the pearl onions and bacon for 2-3 minutes, or until lightly coloured.Add the carrots, artichokes, turnips, mushrooms and radishes and gently fry for 1-2 minutes, then add the garlic. Increase the heat, add the wine and cook for 1-2 minutes, or until the volume of the liquid has reduced by half. Add the stock and reduce the heat to a simmer.Cover the pan with a lid and cook for 3-4 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender. Remove the lid, increase the heat to high and cook for a further 3-4 minutes, or until the liquid has reduced to a thick glaze.Stir in the chopped parsley and season, to taste, with salt and freshly ground black pepper.To serve, spoon the vegetables into a bowl and serve with crusty bread on the side.